<p>I'm trying to use the INFINITY macro as an integer but for some reason it returns 0.</p>  <pre><code>for (int i = 0 ; i&lt;100; i++) {     NSLog(@"%@",[NSNumber numberWithInt:INFINITY]); //return -/+ max int }  for (int i = 0 ; i&lt;100; i++) {     NSLog(@"%@",[NSNumber numberWithFloat:INFINITY]); //return "inf" } </code></pre>  <p>What's the proper usage of INFINITY? I thought it'd return a maximum integer or float value and -INFINITY would return a negative minimum integer or float value but definitely not 0. Why does it return 0?</p>